  "implementationSummary": "Added public GET /v1/auth/tiktok/business/callback for TikTok Marketing API advertiser OAuth. Validates code+state, HMAC-verifies state for Juli user binding, exchanges auth_code via business-api.tiktok.com/open_api/v1.3/oauth2/access_token/, and persists encrypted tokens on existing tiktok_credentials with capability=business_advertiser and merchant_authorization_id=advertiser_id. Shop OAuth path untouched.",
  "assumptions": [
    "Business OAuth state is always present (unlike Shop App Review flow) because credentials must bind to a Juli user.",
    "First advertiser_id in token response is the primary merchant_authorization_id key.",
    "User without shops gets a placeholder TikTok Business shop row for the required shop_id FK.",
    "Marketing API access token expiry uses access_token_expires_at default when field absent (24h TTL assumption)."
  ],
  "risks": [
    "Multi-advertiser authorizations store only the first advertiser_id; future work may need multi-row or list persistence.",
    "Placeholder shop creation for users without shops may need UX alignment when Connect Ads UI lands."
